Put a #large saucepan{} of water with a pinch of @salt{pinch} on to boil for the
@penne pasta{200%g}. Trim the @courgette{1/2}(quartered lengthways and cut into 
small pieces). Halve the @black olives{15}. Finely chop the @chives{1}(finely 
chopped).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat and
once hot, add the courgette and the olives and let cook, stirring often, 
~{3-4%minutes}. Next, add the @dried oregano{1} to the pan, stir well to combine
then add the @tomatoes with onion and garlic{1}(finely chopped), @water for the
sauce{200%ml} and @vegetable stock powder{1/2}, stir well to dissolve.

Bring the sauce to the boil, reduce the heat to a gentle simmer and let it bubble
away and reduce slightly, ~{12-15%minutes}.

When the pan of water is boiling, add the wheat penne and cook for ~{10%minutes}.
Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan off the heat. Drizzle
with oil to stop it sticking together and set aside. Meanwhile, add the
@wild rocket{40%g}, @balsamic vinegar{12%ml}, a drizzle of oil and a pinch of
@salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch} to a #mixing bowl{}. Toss to combine and
set aside - this is your salad.

Once the sauce is ready, add the wheat pasta and most of the chives to the
#frying pan{}. Crumble in half the @feta cheese{100%g}. Remove from the heat and
fold through to combine. Taste to check for seasoning and add salt and pepper
if necessary.

Divide the wheat pasta between bowls and crumble over the remaining feta.
Sprinkle over the last of the chives and arrange the rocket salad alongside.
Dig in!